    <div class="git General">
      <h3>1ST COMPLAINT: DIFFICULTY IN SWALLOWING (Dysphagia)</h3>
      <!-- S: Site -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Site</span>
        <span class="verbal">"When you swallow, where do you feel the food
          getting stuck? Can you point to your neck, or is it lower down in your
          chest?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>HIGH UP (Neck / Pharyngeal): <b class="cns git">Oropharyngeal
              Dysphagia</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="cns">Neuromuscular cause (Stroke, Parkinson's,
                Myasthenia Gravis)</li>
              <li class="git oncology">Pharyngeal Pouch (Zenker's), Head/Neck
                Cancer</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>LOWER DOWN (Chest / Retrosternal): <b class="git">Esophageal
              Dysphagia</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="git">Stricture, Ring, <b class="oncology">Tumor</b>, <b
                  class="rheumatic">Achalasia</b></li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- O: Onset -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>O</strong>: Onset</span>
        <span class="verbal">"When did this difficulty first start? Did it come
          on suddenly or has it been a gradual process?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>SUDDEN: <span class="git emergency">Food bolus impaction, Foreign
              body</span></li>
          <li>GRADUAL (over weeks to months): <span class="git oncology">Stricture,
              <b class="oncology">Malignancy</b>, <b class="rheumatic">Motility
                disorder</b></span></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- D: Duration -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>D</strong>: Duration</span>
        <span class="verbal">"How long has this been a problem for you?"</span>
      </li>
      <!-- A/R: Aggravating / Relieving Factors -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>A/R</strong>:
          Aggravating &amp; Relieving Factors</span> <span class="verbal">"Does
          anything make it better or worse? For example, changing your posture
          or drinking water?"</span> </li>
      <!-- C: Character (THE KEY DIFFERENTIATOR) -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>C</strong>:
          Character</span> <span class="verbal">"What gives you the most
          trouble? Is it solids like bread and meat, liquids like water, or
          both?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li><b>SOLIDS ONLY (progressing to liquids later) -&gt; <span class="git oncology">Suggests
                Mechanical Obstruction</span></b>
            <ul>
              <li class="git">Peptic Stricture</li>
              <li class="git">Schatzki Ring</li>
              <li class="oncology">Esophageal Cancer</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li><b>SOLIDS AND LIQUIDS from the start -&gt; <span class="cns rheumatic git">Suggests
                Motility Disorder</span></b>
            <ul>
              <li class="rheumatic git">Achalasia</li>
              <li class="git">Diffuse Esophageal Spasm</li>
              <li class="rheumatic">Scleroderma</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- R: Radiation (of Pain) -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>:
          Radiation (of Pain)</span> <span class="verbal">"Is it painful when
          you swallow (odynophagia)? If so, does the pain travel anywhere?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="infectious git">Pain suggests inflammation (e.g.,
            Esophagitis from infection or reflux)</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- A: Associated Symptoms -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>A</strong>:
          Associated Symptoms</span> <span class="verbal">"Along with the
          swallowing problem, have you noticed anything else like coughing,
          heartburn, or weight loss?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>OROPHARYNGEAL CLUES:
            <ul>
              <li class="cns respiratory">Coughing, choking, or sputtering
                during meals</li>
              <li class="cns ent">Nasal regurgitation</li>
              <li class="cns ent">Hoarseness or a 'gurgly' voice after
                swallowing</li>
              <li class="cns">Drooling or difficulty initiating a swallow</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>ESOPHAGEAL CLUES:
            <ul>
              <li class="git"><b>Heartburn </b>/ Acid reflux (suggests peptic
                stricture)</li>
              <li class="git">Regurgitation of undigested food hours after
                eating (suggests achalasia, diverticulum)</li>
              <li class="cvs git">Chest pain</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>SYSTEMIC CLUES:
            <ul>
              <li class="oncology">Unexplained weight loss</li>
              <li class="hematology">Symptoms of anemia (fatigue,
                breathlessness)</li>
              <li class="rheumatic">Skin changes (tightening), Raynaud's
                phenomenon (Scleroderma)</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- P: Progression -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>:
          Progression</span> <span class="verbal">"Since it started, has it
          been getting worse, staying the same, or does it come and go?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>PROGRESSIVE: <b class="oncology git">Red flag for malignancy or
              worsening stricture</b></li>
          <li>INTERMITTENT: <span class="git">Suggests a benign ring or web
              (e.g., Schatzki ring)</span></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- P: Pattern -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>: Pattern</span>
        <span class="verbal">"Is there any pattern to it? For example, does it
          happen with every meal?"</span> </li>
      <!-- E: Effect on life -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>E</strong>: Effect
          on Life</span> <span class="verbal">"How has this affected your
          eating habits? Have you lost any weight because of it?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>Fear of eating / Avoiding certain foods</li>
          <li>Social isolation (avoiding meals out)</li>
          <li class="respiratory">Recurrent chest infections (suggests
            aspiration)</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- R: Red Flags -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>: Red
          Flags</span> <span class="verbal">"I just need to ask some specific
          questions to make sure we're not missing anything serious."</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="oncology"><b>Unexplained weight loss</b></li>
          <li class="oncology git"><b>Progressive dysphagia (solids then
              liquids)</b></li>
          <li class="oncology General">New onset of symptoms in a person &gt; 50
            years old</li>
          <li class="hematology git">Signs of GI bleeding (e.g., iron-deficiency
            anemia)</li>
          <li class="ent cns oncology">Associated hoarseness, which can indicate
            recurrent laryngeal nerve involvement</li>
          <li class="oncology">Palpable lymph nodes</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- S: Scale -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Severity
          / Bother Scale</span> <span class="verbal">"On a scale of 1 to 10,
          how much does this difficulty in swallowing affect your life?"</span>
      </li>
    </div>
